\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Theorem
Soppose 
\begin_inset Formula $(X,Y)$
\end_inset

 has joint pdf 
\begin_inset Formula $f(x,y)$
\end_inset

 , let 
\begin_inset Formula $U=g(X,Y),\ V=h(X,Y)$
\end_inset

 be one to one functions.
 Then the joint pdf of 
\begin_inset Formula $(U,V)$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
f_{UV}(u,v)=f(x,y)\ {\rm abs}|J|
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula ${\rm abs}|J|$
\end_inset

 refers to the absolute value of Jacobian 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
|J|=\left|\begin{array}{cc}
\frac{\partial x}{\partial u} & \frac{\partial x}{\partial v}\\
\frac{\partial y}{\partial u} & \frac{\partial y}{\partial v}
\end{array}\right|
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_deeper
